  <title>CBM:Improving Children&apos;s eye care in Malawi</title>
  <description>Malawi has a shortage of eye care specialists. This project aims to improve provision through the establishment of a children&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s eye care centre, based in Blantyre and supported by a network of community-based health workers and a referral service for Lilongwe. Ophthalmologists with paediatrics as a sub-specialty and Ophthalmic Clinical Officers will be trained. Equipment for examining children with visual disabilities will be provided, and a referral system and protocol for the management of children with cataracts and other serious eye conditions will be established.</description>
